    "chain_to_addresses": {
      "1": [
        "0x39053d51b77dc0d36036fc1fcc8cb819df8ef37a"
      ]
    }
  },
  "note": "Batch variant: array_emit over withdrawals[]. The parallel receiveAsTokens bool[] is index-aligned with withdrawals[] and IS decoded per-element via emit.parallel_sources: the synthetic `receiveAsTokens` parallel binds receiveAsTokens[i] to $inputs.receiveAsTokens, while the Withdrawal tuple binds via $inputs.element[..]. So receive_as_tokens is populated for every batch leg, identical to the single completeQueuedWithdrawal — the receive-as-shares trap is caught on batch too. (parallel_sources is the same mechanism Permit2 permitTransferFromBatch uses for its index-aligned TokenPermissions[]/SignatureTransferDetails[].) Separately, each Withdrawal's scaledShares (idx 6) — the amount completed — remains in protocol-internal scaled-share units (§4d illegible) and is intentionally NOT decoded (raw scaled-share is user-illegible; underlying conversion needs a per-strategy rate + slashing scaling factor, array-shaped, not manifest-only); per §4d a justified defer (documented so the omission is a decision, not a silent drop, §8.6-5).",
  "abi_fragment": {
    "function_name": "completeQueuedWithdrawals",
    "abi": {
      "inputs": [
        {
          "components": [
            {
              "internalType": "address",
              "name": "staker",
              "type": "address"
            },
            {
              "internalType": "address",
              "name": "delegatedTo",
              "type": "address"
            },
            {
              "internalType": "address",
              "name": "withdrawer",
              "type": "address"
            },
            {
              "internalType": "uint256",
              "name": "nonce",
              "type": "uint256"
            },
            {
              "internalType": "uint32",
              "name": "startBlock",
              "type": "uint32"
            },
            {
              "internalType": "contract IStrategy[]",
              "name": "strategies",
              "type": "address[]"
            },
            {
              "internalType": "uint256[]",
              "name": "scaledShares",
              "type": "uint256[]"
            }
          ],
          "internalType": "struct IDelegationManagerTypes.Withdrawal[]",
          "name": "withdrawals",
          "type": "tuple[]"
        },
        {
          "internalType": "contract IERC20[][]",
          "name": "tokens",
          "type": "address[][]"
        },
        {
          "internalType": "bool[]",
          "name": "receiveAsTokens",
          "type": "bool[]"
        }
      ],
      "name": "completeQueuedWithdrawals",
      "outputs": [],
      "stateMutability": "nonpayable",
      "type": "function"
    }
  },
  "emit": {
    "strategy": "array_emit",
    "array_source": "$args.withdrawals",
    "parallel_sources": {
      "receiveAsTokens": "$args.receiveAsTokens"
    },
    "body": {
      "domain": "restaking",
      "restaking": {
        "action": "complete_withdrawal",
        "complete_withdrawal": {
          "venue": {
            "name": "eigenlayer",
            "chain": "$chain"
          },
          "staker": "$inputs.element[0]",
          "withdrawer": "$inputs.element[2]",
          "strategies": "$inputs.element[5]",
          "receive_as_tokens": "$inputs.receiveAsTokens"
        }
      }
    },
    "live_inputs": {}
  },
